    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"My personal Website"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f8d50173-8832-5df8-ac57-dd7f83e31e2c","excerpt":"useful in spaces that have dimensions Euclidian spaces Discrete euclidian spaces (i.e vectors of integers, vector of bools) … Points are thought as directions…","html":"<ul>\n<li>useful in spaces that have dimensions\n<ul>\n<li>Euclidian spaces</li>\n<li>Discrete euclidian spaces (i.e vectors of integers, vector of bools)</li>\n<li>…</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Points are thought as <em>directions</em></li>\n<li>No distinction between a vector and a multiple of it</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The Cosine Distance between two points is the <em>angle</em> that the vectors to these points make</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>The angle will be between <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>0</mn><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">∘</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0^{\\circ}</annotation></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>18</mn><msup><mn>0</mn><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">∘</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">180^{\\circ}</annotation></semantics></math></span></span> regardless of <em>how many dimensions</em> the space has</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>d</mi><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>a</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>b</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>a</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>b</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>a</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>⋅</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>b</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac><mrow><msubsup><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></msubsup><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>⋅</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>a</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>⋅</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>b</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∥</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">d_{cos}(\\vec a, \\vec b) = arcos  \\left ( \\frac{\\vec a \\cdot \\vec b}{\\| \\vec a \\|_2 \\cdot \\| \\vec b \\|_2}  \\right )  = arcos  \\left ( \\frac{\\sum_{i=1}^na_i \\cdot b_i}{\\| \\vec a \\|_2 \\cdot \\| \\vec b \\|_2} \\right )</annotation></semantics></math></span></span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Cosine Distance","tags":["Data Minig","ETH"],"category":"Mathematics"},"headings":[]}},"pageContext":{"id":"f8d50173-8832-5df8-ac57-dd7f83e31e2c","previousPost":{"title":"L2-Norm","slug":"/blog/l2_norm"},"nextPost":{"title":"Open Source Software","slug":"/blog/open_source"},"dates":{"created":1452269256,"modified":1647509701}}},
